üñ•Ô∏è System Info Commands
| Command          | Description                                |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `uname -a`       | Prints all system info (kernel, OS, arch)  |
| `hostname`       | Displays or sets the system's hostname     |
| `uptime`         | Shows system uptime                        |
| `top`            | Displays real-time system processes        |
| `htop`           | Advanced version of `top` (needs install)  |
| `df -h`          | Shows disk space usage                     |
| `du -sh folder/` | Shows folder size                          |
| `free -h`        | Displays RAM and swap memory usage         |
| `lscpu`          | Detailed CPU information                   |
| `lsblk`          | Lists block devices (e.g., disks)          |
| `whoami`         | Current logged-in user                     |
| `id`             | Shows UID, GID, and groups of current user |
